# Online Shopping Cart (Java)

## Project Overview
The **Online Shopping Cart** is a Java console-based application that allows users to browse products, add items to cart, remove items, and generate a final bill.  
This project demonstrates the use of **Object-Oriented Programming concepts** and Java collections to simulate a basic e-commerce workflow.

## Features
- View available products
- Add and remove items from cart
- Generate bill with total amount
- Quantity-based calculation

## Concepts Used
| Concept | Usage |
|---------|--------|
| Encapsulation | Product details are private fields |
| Classes & Objects | `Product`, `Cart`, `ShoppingApp` classes |
| ArrayList | Stores cart items dynamically |
| Methods | `addToCart()`, `removeFromCart()`, `generateBill()` |
